text: Nectandra paranaensis is a species of plant in the family Lauraceae. It is endemic to Paraná (state) and São Paulo (state) in Brazil. It is a Vulnerable species, threatened by habitat loss. ==References== paranaensis Category:Endemic flora of Brazil Category:Flora of Paraná (state) Category:Flora of São Paulo (state) Category:Vulnerable flora of South America Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
